<TEXT>
   Sammy Davis Jr. says his wife, Altovise, and
Barbara Sinatra helped him kick drugs by enlisting the aid of his
Rat Pack buddy, Frank Sinatra.
   ``Because of her love, I had a second chance,'' he said of his
wife. ``Because of her, I've found my friendships have grown deeper
and more substantial.''
   Davis, who was diagnosed last week with throat cancer, says he
was driven to drugs by ``a terrible insecurity'' but stopped using
them after meeting with Sinatra.
