<TEXT>
   Giovanni Migliuolo, Italy's permanent
representative to the United Nations, died Wednesday of a brain
tumor at the age of 62.
   Migliuolo was one of the Italian government's experts on
East-West politics and was a scholar of Slavic languages and culture.
   He was Italy's ambassador to Moscow from 1981 to 1985, also
serving as ambassador to Mongolia. From 1985 to 1988, Migliuolo was
the ambassador to Cairo. He became the senior U.N. ambassador a year
ago.
