<HEAD>President Declares Disaster in South Carolina</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush today declared that a ``major
disaster'' exists in South Carolina and ordered federal aid to help
recovery efforts in the area ravaged by Hurricane Hugo.
   Bush's disaster declaration covers a seven-county area along the
storm's path. Such a declaration makes a variety of federal aid
available to governments, businesses and individuals.
