<HEAD>NPR Changes Announced</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Liane Hansen, current host of National Public
Radio's ``Performance Today'' show, will replace Sunday ``Weekend
Edition'' host Susan Stamberg, who is becoming a special
correspondent, NPR said today.
   Hansen will take her new job Nov. 5 on the news magazine show,
according to Adam Powell, NPR vice president for news and
information.
   Hansen has more than 15 years experience as a radio producer,
reporter and on-air host. She has been a regular guest host on both
``All Things Considered'' on weekends and ``Weekend Edition'' on
Sundays, as well as for ``Fresh Air'' with Terry Gross.
   Stamberg, who has hosted ``Weekend Edition'' since its debut in
January 1987, will leave the show Oct. 29 and take up her new duties
Nov. 1. She has been with NPR for 17 years.
   Stamberg previously co-hosted the weekday version of the ``All
Things Considered'' news magazine show for 14 years.
   Powell said Stamberg's first assignment will be ``Shanghai and
the Jews,'' a series of reports about the World War II experience of
Jews who fled Nazi Germany for Shanghai.
