<SECOND>AM-BRF--Journalist-Bomb,0139</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bomb Explodes Under Journalist's Car</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALGHERO, Sardinia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded under the car of a
journalist on this Italian island Friday, damaging several vehicles
but not injuring anyone, police said.
   The car destroyed by the bomb was parked in front of the Alghero
home of Gianni Olandi, a reporter for the daily La Nuova Sardegna,
based in nearby Sassari.
   Olandi recently wrote a series of articles about building
speculation on Sardinia, a popular tourist destination. Local
officials have moved to limit construction near the island's beaches.
   Several other cars were damaged and windows of nearby buildings
were blown out by the early morning blast, police said.
   A police officer, speaking on condition of anonymity, said
Olandi's car was apparently targeted because of his work. No arrests
had been made, he said.
