<HEAD>Former Labor Leader's Family Doubts Playboy Story</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The daughter of former Teamster leader Jimmy
Hoffa says she was shocked by a magazine article about how her
father was killed and dismembered, but she doubts the story is true.
   ``It's terribly gory. It's terribly upsetting to the entire
family,'' Barbara Ann Crancer said after reading an advance of the
article in Playboy. ``It's a hame we had to read it in a
Playboy-type magazine.''
