<HEAD>Swiss End Inquiry Into Deliveries to Libyan Plant</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERN, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Swiss companies acted legally in helping
Libya build a chemical plant the United States claimed could make
poison gas, the Federal Prosecutor's Office said Friday.
   It said it had dropped its investigation.
   Officials refused to reveal the names of the firms investigated.
   The United States said it had evidence the factory near Rabta,
Libya, about 35 miles outside Tripoli, was on the verge of producing
chemical weapons. Libya said the plant was for pharmaceutical
production.
