<FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks 1stLd-Writethru   09-22 0164</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0169</SECOND>
<HEAD>London Shares Close Lower</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES with close</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stocks closed moderately lower in light trading
Friday amid an exodus of buyers before the Group of Seven meeting in
Washington this weekend.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed down
10.7 points, or 0.4 percent, at 2,370.2, just above its session low
of 2,369.7, and well below the day's high of 2,382.1.
   Volume was a light 452.9 million shares, compared with 413.8
million shares Thursday.
   Besides concerns over potential action by the G-7, dealers said
limited action on Wall Street gave little direction to London.
   The G-7 nations are the United States, West Germany, Japan,
France, Britain, Italy and Canada.
   The major feature of the session was Boots Co. PLC, the British
health-care retailer and pharmaceuticals concern, which fell 41
cents to $4.55 a share after the company said clinical trials of a
heart drug showed it was less successful than expected in treating
congestive heart failure.
</TEXT>
