<FIRST>r f AM-MortgageRates     09-22 0070</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mortgage Rates,0074</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fixed-Rate Mortgages Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages are averaging 10.03
percent, according to a national survey released Friday by the
Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp.
   That rate was down from a rate of 10.05 percent last week.
   On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 8.70 percent this week, up from 8.68 percent
the week before, Freddie Mac said.
</TEXT>
