<FIRST>r f AM-Anchor-Vitro     09-22 0313</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Anchor-Vitro,0326</SECOND>
<HEAD>Anchor Says It's For Sale as Vitro Extends Tender Deadline</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Anchor Glass Container Corp. directors have
agreed to seek a buyer for the nation's second-largest glass maker
in an attempt to thwart a unsolicited $280 million takeover bid from
a Mexican company.
   Anchor spokesman Thomas Davies on Friday said several suitors
have expressed interest in buying the entire company since the
hostile bid was launched last month by a subsidiary of Vitro SA,
which has extended its $20-a-share offer until Sept. 28.
   Davies would not identify any of the parties interested in
Anchor, whose board has urged shareholders to reject the offer by
Vitro, one of Mexico's major glass manufacturers.
   A committee of Anchor directors said a sale could be completed by
the end of October.
   ``Obviously, there cannot be any guarantee a sale will take
place,'' said Davies.
   Vitro, based in Monterrey, Mexico, announced Friday its
subsidiary, THR Corp., has been tendered about 72 percent of the
13.9 million Anchor shares outstanding. THR and its affiliates owned
about 1.43 million shares before the tender offer was announced.
   In trading Friday on the New York Stock Exchange, Anchor rose 37{
cents a share to $19.37{. It was trading below $10 a share before
the tender offer was announced.
   In a news release late Thursday, a committee of Anchor directors
said that ``based upon the interests indicated to date by third
parties, it has determined that a sale of the company in its
entirety is the method most likely to succeed in maximizing
shareholder values at this time.''
   A Vitro spokeswoman declined to comment on its plans or Anchor's
announcement.
   Vitro has filed a suit in Delaware Chancery Court challenging
Anchor's anti-takeover defenses.
   Anchor lost $8.5 million last year on sales of $977.8 million,
while Vitro earned more than $150 million on revenues of nearly $1.1
billion.
</TEXT>
